    {
        "content": "<p>I tried the code with the correct syntax (<code>def Category : Cat where  Obj := Cat ...</code> or <code>{ Obj := Cat, ... }</code> but Lean reports universe error. I realized the problem is that even though <code>Cat</code> is one universe higher, <code>Fun</code> is in the original universe, so you either need to allow different universes for <code>Obj</code> and <code>Hom</code>, or else need to specify the universe of <code>Fun</code> to be one higher.</p>",
        "id": 321541323,
        "sender_full_name": "Junyan Xu",
        "timestamp": 1673825557
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>something like</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">structure</span> <span class=\"n\">Fun</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">C</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">Cat.</span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">u</span><span class=\"o\">})</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">D</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">Cat.</span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">u</span><span class=\"o\">})</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">u</span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"n\">where</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
